  p Tab labels can either each be placed next to their respective content (as in the example code above), or they can be separate &ndash; e.g. all the labels grouped together first in the #[code tabs] container.

  h3 X-Axis Scrolling on Tab Labels
  
  p If you group all the tab labels together as above, you have the option to wrap them in a container with class #[code tab__label-wrap]. This container prevents the tabs from wrapping to a newline (when there are more tabs than the viewport width allows on row of labels), and allows x-axis scrolling.
    
